{
  "texts": [
    "Correction: We then sampled and examined a subset of 20 annotated papers.",
    "Following this, we decided to apply some automatic rules to fix the annotations: (1) We merged the 'computer science' field with the 'NLP' field;",
    "(2) For the mechanism annotation, we replaced internal components with 'internal-internal', and representations with 'input-internal';",
    "(3) Many of the scope annotations were 'unknown'.",
    "In these cases, we replaced 'unknown' with 'local' for feature attributions and natural language explanation paradigms and with 'global' for probing, diagnostic sets, and mechanistic interpretability paradigms; (4) We replaced 'unknown' values of the accessibility annotations with 'model-specific' for the SHAP/LIME, probing and mechanistic interpretability paradigms, and with 'model-agnostic' for the diagnostic sets paradigm."
  ]
}